  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Harrow Reader",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Cosmic Caravan",
              "aonid": 377,
              "game-obj": "Deities",
              "name": "Cosmic Caravan",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "demons",
              "aonid": 387,
              "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
              "name": "demons",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Forms Of Fortune-Telling",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                "aonid": 236,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "NPC Core",
              "page": 96,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "**Anthomancy**: flowers  \n **Astrology**: the Cosmic Caravan  \n **Astromancy**: movement and brightness of stars  \n **Chiromancy**: reading the palm's heart, life, and head lines  \n **Demonomancy**: asking demons  \n **Harrowing**: harrow card readings  \n **Haruspicy**: entrails  \n **Ichthyomancy**: the next fish caught  \n **Mazomancy**: a nursing babe  \n **Oneiromancy**: dreams  \n **Pendulum Reading**: answering yes or no questions with a pendulum  \n **Pyromancy**: throwing substances into fire  \n **Tasseomancy**: tea leaves  \n **Tyromancy**: coagulation of cheese",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
            "aonid": 236,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "NPC Core",
          "page": 96,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "A harrow deck is a set of 54 cards with symbolic illustrations that serves as a sacred divining tool. Feared by the superstitious and avoided by those who know better than to tempt fate, many harrow readers live and work in traveling communities, often moving from town to town as opportunities arise.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
