              },
              {
                "alt": "tripkee fiend keeper",
                "aonid": 3675,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "tripkee fiend keeper",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Crossover Ancestry NPCs",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 96,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Several of the NPCs elsewhere in NPC Core can fit well in this group: Bone mother (level 6), gourd leshy witch (level 6), tripkee fiend keeper (level 7)",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "name": "Guests Beware",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 96,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Most intelligent creatures follow basic customs of hospitality, such as not attacking a guest who has dined under their roof. Even the most sinister fey creature is loath to break such customs, though eating meals with the fey is often fraught with its own dangers. Others have fewer scruples and might employ poisons, curses, or potions as seasoning for unwitting dinner guests.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "bodyguard",
                "aonid": 3513,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "bodyguard",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "archer sentry",
                "aonid": 3552,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "archer sentry",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "musketeer",
                "aonid": 3507,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "musketeer",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "tournament combatant",
                "aonid": 3501,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "tournament combatant",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "knight",
                "aonid": 3423,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "knight",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "hero hunter",
                "aonid": 3621,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "hero hunter",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Mystic Protection",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 96,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Most mystics aren't particularly skilled in combat and might hire or ensorcel bodyguards, such as the bodyguard (level 1), archer sentry (level 2), musketeer (level 3), tournament combatant (level 5), knight (level 7), or hero hunter (level 13).",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "angelic messenger",
                "aonid": 141,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "angelic messenger",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "binding circle",
                "aonid": 110,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "binding circle",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "call spirit",
                "aonid": 112,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "call spirit",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "collective memories",
                "aonid": 113,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "collective memories",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "commune",
                "aonid": 114,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "commune",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "demonic pact",
                "aonid": 142,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "demonic pact",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "diabolic pact",
                "aonid": 143,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "diabolic pact",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "planar servitor",
                "aonid": 120,
                "game-obj": "Rituals",
                "name": "planar servitor",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Mystic Rituals",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 96,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The following are rituals sometimes cast by mystic groups. Those from *Monster Core* are available only to appropriate celestials and fiends within the organizations. \n* *angelic messenger* (1st rank)\n* *binding circle* (6th rank)\n* *call spirit* (5th rank)\n* *collective memories* (9th rank)\n* *commune* (6th rank)\n* *demonic pact* (1st rank)\n* *diabolic pact* (1st rank)\n* *planar servitor* (5th rank)",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "name": "Sinister Rituals",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 96,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Most rituals have a simple gp cost and associated skill checks. But what if a desperate NPC is willing to offer something more macabre, such as lives, souls, or worse? Such a nefarious ritual uses a normal ritual as a baseline, but the DCs and proficiency requirements might be reduced or waived entirely, as might any gp cost.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "NPC Core pg. 96",
              "aonid": 236,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "NPC Core pg. 96",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "NPC Core",
            "page": 96,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Hidden secrets and occult powers have an irresistible lure for many. Since the majority of these NPCs are spellcasters, consider using alternative spell lists to adjust their themes.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
